Do you know
what a fat chance is?

01:45.110 --> 01:47.560
Oh, save some roast beef
for your father, dear.

01:47.560 --> 01:49.110
He'll be home any minute.

01:49.530 --> 01:52.110
Oh, did he get hung up
at the Leopard Lodge again?

01:52.110 --> 01:53.610
Yes, he's working
very hard

01:53.610 --> 01:56.120
being chairman of the
Leopard's Demolition Derby.

01:56.120 --> 01:57.900
So be nice to your
father; he's tired.

01:58.120 --> 02:00.650
Oh, I will, but then can I go
over to Ginny Pickalow's house?

02:01.070 --> 02:02.160
Yes, yes, of course.

02:02.160 --> 02:03.160
Good.

02:03.160 --> 02:06.160
Hark, hark, the chairman of
the Demolition Derby is home.

02:09.660 --> 02:11.160
And have I got
something to show you.

02:11.660 --> 02:12.670
Yeah, congratulations,
Dad.

02:13.170 --> 02:14.670
I'll see you
later, all right?
Yeah, I'm happy too.

02:14.670 --> 02:15.670
Well, I'll be on my way.

02:15.670 --> 02:17.170
No, no, no, wait a minute.

02:17.170 --> 02:18.670
Come on, now,
everybody sit down.

02:18.670 --> 02:21.170
I got something very big
to share with you.

02:21.170 --> 02:24.180
Right here,
in this box,

02:24.180 --> 02:26.060
is one of the
highlights of my life.

02:26.400 --> 02:27.480
Oh, let me see.

02:27.480 --> 02:29.480
Is there a picture of you
with your tummy all tucked in?

02:32.940 --> 02:35.860
You're gonna do fat jokes in the
middle of a man's highlights?

02:36.190 --> 02:37.240
I'm sorry.

02:37.660 --> 02:39.740
It happens to be
the publicity leaflet

02:39.740 --> 02:41.740
for the Demolition Derby.

02:42.250 --> 02:44.250
"The Leopard's First Annual
Team Demolition Derby

02:44.250 --> 02:46.500
"will be held next Tuesday
at Pfister National Park.

02:46.700 --> 02:48.280
"It will feature great
demolition drivers

02:48.280 --> 02:50.750
"like Arthur Fonzarelli and
his partner Nookie Newman,

02:51.170 --> 02:52.540
and the..."
Dad, we know that.

02:52.790 --> 02:53.870
Would you be patient?

02:53.870 --> 02:55.180
Go on, Howard.

02:55.380 --> 02:56.960
Okay.
"Now, to kick off the derby,

02:56.960 --> 03:00.460
"the Leopards present a driving
exhibition by Pinky Tuscadero,

03:00.460 --> 03:03.470
the world's greatest female
cyclist, and her Pinkettes."

03:03.880 --> 03:04.970
Oh, she is marvelous.

03:04.970 --> 03:06.970
I just can't wait to see her
do those Poppa wheelies

03:06.970 --> 03:07.970
and those wild jumps.

03:07.970 --> 03:09.440
(imitates engine revving)

03:12.390 --> 03:13.480
Dad, Fonzie and Pinky
are old friends.

03:13.480 --> 03:14.440
HOWARD:
Yeah.

03:14.810 --> 03:15.900
"All proceeds..."
I think Fonzie's

03:15.900 --> 03:16.900
looking forward to seeing her.

03:16.900 --> 03:17.900
"All proceeds..."
Yeah.

03:17.900 --> 03:20.900
He got four of
his T-shirts pressed.

03:20.900 --> 03:21.900
Do you mind?

03:21.900 --> 03:22.900
Oh, go ahead, Dad.
Oh, go ahead.

03:22.900 --> 03:24.400
This is very
interesting, dear.
We're waiting.

03:26.540 --> 03:29.630
"All proceeds of the Demolition
Derby go to charity.

03:30.130 --> 03:33.130
"The entire event is sponsored
by the Milwaukee Leopard Lodge.

03:33.130 --> 03:36.970
Chairman of the event,
Leopard Howard Cunningham."

03:37.250 --> 03:37.830
Oh, that's great.

03:38.330 --> 03:39.340
Well, I'm going
to Ginny's.

03:39.840 --> 03:40.840
Yeah, thanks a lot, Dad.

03:40.840 --> 03:41.840
I'll read it later, okay?

03:41.840 --> 03:43.340
That's wonderful.

03:43.340 --> 03:44.840
JOANIE:
Oh, hope you get
the job, Richie.

03:44.840 --> 03:47.340
What later?

03:47.340 --> 03:49.350
I mean, the kids
on <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Father Knows Bes{\r}t</font></font></i>

03:49.350 --> 03:51.310
never walk out
on Robert Young.

03:55.820 --> 03:57.400
Hey, Fonz.

03:59.490 --> 04:00.490
Need some help, Fonz?

04:00.770 --> 04:01.860
Hey, listen, you guys,

04:01.860 --> 04:03.360
will you please
stick to the stand?

04:03.360 --> 04:05.660
It takes you an hour to
knock in one solitary nail.

04:05.860 --> 04:07.280
I hurt my thumb.

04:07.500 --> 04:08.580
Oh, yeah?

04:08.580 --> 04:09.950
You want me to
kiss that boo-boo?

04:11.250 --> 04:14.620
Good evening, gentlemen,
and all the ships at sea.

04:14.870 --> 04:15.960
All right,
Richie got the TV job!

04:15.960 --> 04:16.959
Yeah, I got it!
Okay!

04:16.959 --> 04:17.959
Yeah.
Great.

04:17.959 --> 04:19.430
All right, all right,
listen to this.

04:19.430 --> 04:21.459
Flash, this is
Rick Cunningham

04:21.459 --> 04:24.960
bringing you the Demolition
Derby live on WZAZ-TV.

04:24.960 --> 04:25.930
(chuckles)
Okay.

04:26.300 --> 04:27.680
Rick?

04:27.880 --> 04:29.850
You don't like Rick?

04:30.140 --> 04:32.110
Is your father's
name Ozzie?

04:32.390 --> 04:34.970
Yeah, right.

04:34.970 --> 04:35.980
Scratch Rick.

04:35.980 --> 04:37.860
Oh, oh, Fonz,
I got a message for you.

04:38.190 --> 04:40.780
Well, bring
it over here.

04:40.780 --> 04:41.780
Pinky was
over at the station,

04:42.280 --> 04:44.780
and she said she was going to be
by later with the Pinkettes.

04:44.780 --> 04:45.790
Oh, that's great.
Thanks a lot.

04:45.790 --> 04:47.790
Yeah-- oh, oh, right,
right, pictures.

04:47.790 --> 04:49.070
I got another
message for you.

04:49.290 --> 04:52.210
You're a regular little
courier pigeon, aren't you?

04:52.490 --> 04:54.580
No, no, see, they're,
they're letting me

04:54.580 --> 04:56.580
do this special feature
on all the derby drivers.

04:56.580 --> 04:57.580
I need a good
picture of you.

04:58.080 --> 04:59.080
Well, I got some
pictures inside.

04:59.080 --> 05:00.580
Well, now, it's got
to be a very good one.

05:01.000 --> 05:04.420
Hey, could this face
take a bad picture?

05:04.670 --> 05:06.760
Oh, no, I guess not.

05:06.760 --> 05:08.260
This is Richie Cunningham...

05:08.260 --> 05:09.760
You want to
get in here?

05:09.760 --> 05:11.180
Oh...
(motorcycles approaching)

05:11.510 --> 05:13.100
Hey, the Pinkettes
are here already.
Yeah, yeah.

05:13.100 --> 05:14.100
Let old Malph handle this.

05:14.100 --> 05:16.100
Okay. Do I look okay?
Yeah, perfect.

05:16.100 --> 05:17.600
Hiya, guys.

05:17.600 --> 05:18.600
Hi.
Hi, girls.

05:18.600 --> 05:20.100
Hi.
RALPH: You must be
the Pinkettes, huh?

05:20.100 --> 05:21.400
Mm-hmm.
Mm-hmm.

05:21.600 --> 05:22.570
Is that Pinky's bike?

05:22.820 --> 05:24.690
Well, it's not Blackie's.

05:24.990 --> 05:26.580
Okay.
Go ahead.

05:26.580 --> 05:27.530
(clears throat)

05:27.910 --> 05:30.000
Hi, girls.
(chuckles)

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
I'm a singer.

05:32.000 --> 05:32.780
You're boring.

05:33.080 --> 05:34.670
Oh, you've already
met Potsie.

05:37.620 --> 05:38.710
Hey, I love singers.

05:39.210 --> 05:40.170
Yeah?
Mm-hmm.

05:40.540 --> 05:43.130
Hey, uh, I'm going to be
singing "America the Beautiful."

05:43.130 --> 05:44.630
Ah.

05:44.630 --> 05:45.600
♪ Oh, beautiful ♪

05:45.960 --> 05:47.010
♪ For spacious skies... ♪

05:47.010 --> 05:48.550
I've heard it.
Oh.

05:50.550 --> 05:52.550
Hi, Red.

05:52.550 --> 05:54.550
Hi, Red.
(chuckles)

05:54.550 --> 05:55.560
You know,
uh, I'm one of

05:55.560 --> 05:57.060
the funniest guys
in the neighborhood.

05:57.060 --> 05:58.060
Oh.

05:58.060 --> 06:00.560
Funny guys
aren't romantic.

06:00.560 --> 06:02.560
Oh-- wait a minute--
don't go.

06:02.560 --> 06:05.060
I'm only funny with the guys;
with you, I'd be real serious.

06:05.060 --> 06:06.480
You know, I'm a very
serious driver.

06:06.870 --> 06:08.450
Oh.
(chuckles)

06:08.450 --> 06:09.400
I like drivers.

06:09.790 --> 06:11.370
You do?
Mm.

06:11.370 --> 06:13.870
Well, let's talk, maybe we'll
find something in common.

06:14.290 --> 06:15.880
(giggles)

06:19.960 --> 06:22.250
(both moan)

06:25.670 --> 06:26.970
(snapping fingers)

06:43.570 --> 06:46.070
(snapping rhythmically)

06:46.410 --> 06:48.440
Hey, Fonz.

06:48.440 --> 06:49.360
Guess who?

06:51.780 --> 06:52.780
Hiya, Pinky.

06:52.780 --> 06:53.780
M-wah!

06:54.280 --> 06:54.780
Long time.

06:55.200 --> 06:56.280
Yeah, a little too long.

06:56.280 --> 06:57.280
Uh-huh.

06:57.670 --> 06:58.250
How you been?

06:58.670 --> 06:59.750
Well, not a hair out of place.

07:00.120 --> 07:00.950
Was there ever?

07:01.200 --> 07:01.790
How you?

07:02.210 --> 07:04.790
(chuckles)

07:04.790 --> 07:05.790
(snaps)

07:05.790 --> 07:07.290
Uh...

07:07.290 --> 07:09.300
I was sort of hoping you
could check out my "sickle."

07:09.300 --> 07:10.210
(snaps)

07:10.550 --> 07:11.630
Oh, yeah.

07:11.630 --> 07:13.430
I'll, uh, I'll check over
your "sickle."

07:13.680 --> 07:15.770
You know, I want you
to be sure and look over,

07:15.770 --> 07:18.050
uh, the points, uh, the pistons.

07:18.300 --> 07:19.390
Sure.

07:19.390 --> 07:23.230
Up, down, all around.

07:24.560 --> 07:26.030
It's a little warm
in here.

