♪ Doo-doo-doo-doo ♪

08:13.940 --> 08:16.910
♪ Ee-ooh ♪

08:16.910 --> 08:19.950
♪ Doo-doo, doo-doo ♪

08:19.950 --> 08:22.950
♪ Doo, doo, doo ♪

08:22.950 --> 08:25.960
♪ Doo-doo-doo-doo ♪

08:25.960 --> 08:29.960
♪ Doo-doo-doo-doo... ♪

08:29.960 --> 08:35.460
♪ Ah, ah, ah, ah ♪

08:35.970 --> 08:40.970
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

08:40.970 --> 08:44.970
♪ Doo-wah... ♪

08:44.970 --> 08:47.480
(lush, orchestral version of
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Happy Days theme playing{\r})</font></font></i>

09:14.000 --> 09:16.010
(rock 'n' roll playing,
rhythmic clapping)

09:24.260 --> 09:26.850
♪ Well, you're all 16 ♪

09:26.850 --> 09:31.850
♪ You're all beautiful,
and you're all mine. ♪

09:31.850 --> 09:33.860
(scatting)

09:34.360 --> 09:35.240
(music fades, applause)

09:36.580 --> 09:38.110
Thank you.

09:44.780 --> 09:47.290
I was supposed to be a driver,
but I got hurt.

09:47.290 --> 09:48.290
But I can play.

09:48.290 --> 09:51.290
(plays riff)

09:51.290 --> 09:53.710
Come on, Ralph, you're not
hurt, you're just faking it.

09:54.010 --> 09:56.100
Ah, well, we certainly
are looking forward

09:56.100 --> 09:58.460
to having you for dinner
tomorrow night, Miss Tuscadero.

09:58.800 --> 09:59.850
I mean,
it's a great honor

10:00.220 --> 10:01.800
to have the guest star

10:01.800 --> 10:03.640
of the Demolition
Derby in our home.

10:03.940 --> 10:06.020
Well, Fonzie and I
would be happy to come,

10:06.020 --> 10:07.470
but you got
to call me Pinky.

10:07.860 --> 10:09.440
Oh, I can't wait
for Tuesday

10:09.440 --> 10:10.440
when you do those
Poppa wheelies.

10:10.940 --> 10:12.450
(imitates revving engine)

10:12.450 --> 10:15.730
Marion, you've got to stop
hanging around Fonzie.

10:15.900 --> 10:16.480
(giggles)

10:16.900 --> 10:18.990
You got some old lady.

10:18.990 --> 10:19.990
(snaps)
Later.

10:21.990 --> 10:22.990
You got some old lady.

10:23.490 --> 10:23.990
(snaps)
Later.

10:24.490 --> 10:24.990
Joanie!

10:25.410 --> 10:26.880
Later?

10:28.330 --> 10:29.580
RICHIE:
Al, come here
for a minute.

10:29.800 --> 10:30.880
Yeah.

10:30.880 --> 10:31.880
Come here. Listen.
Okay.

10:31.880 --> 10:33.880
It was really swell of you
to throw this party

10:33.880 --> 10:34.880
kicking off the derby
and everything.

10:34.880 --> 10:36.250
Oh, it's nothing.

10:36.550 --> 10:38.140
I think you ought to make a
little welcoming speech, huh?

10:38.140 --> 10:39.640
No, I don't like to do that.

10:39.640 --> 10:41.140
Oh, the gang would love
to hear from you, Al.

10:41.140 --> 10:42.140
But I'm too shy.

10:42.640 --> 10:43.640
I'll-I'll introduce you.

10:43.640 --> 10:45.140
(chuckles):
No, don't, don't do that.

10:45.140 --> 10:46.150
Well, okay.

10:46.150 --> 10:49.150
Do it.

10:49.150 --> 10:50.650
And make it humble.

10:50.650 --> 10:52.150
Okay, right.

10:52.150 --> 10:54.650
Ladies and gentlemen,

10:54.650 --> 10:57.160
I'd like to hear a nice
round of applause for the man

10:57.160 --> 10:58.160
who made this
evening possible.

10:58.660 --> 11:01.660
He supplied all the free
pizza and the free soda pop,

11:01.660 --> 11:03.660
so let's hear it for
a nice guy-- Al.

11:03.660 --> 11:06.670
(cheering, applause)

11:06.670 --> 11:08.170
Don't. Oh, no.

11:08.170 --> 11:10.170
Don't, don't,
don't do it.

11:10.670 --> 11:11.670
(chuckles)

11:11.670 --> 11:13.960
Well, everybody enjoy.

11:14.170 --> 11:16.260
Isn't Alfred cute?

11:16.260 --> 11:17.760
Arnold is cute.

11:18.260 --> 11:20.710
Alfred is humble.
And Italian.

11:27.970 --> 11:28.970
What's wrong, Fonz?

11:28.970 --> 11:29.970
(all chattering)

11:29.970 --> 11:31.470
All right, that's it.

11:31.470 --> 11:32.480
I'm not in
the derby anymore.

11:32.980 --> 11:33.860
Why? Why?
Why? What happened?

11:34.190 --> 11:36.280
Because my partner,
Nookie Newman,

11:36.280 --> 11:38.780
just broke his leg
jumping out of a motel window!

11:39.280 --> 11:40.280
Ah, no!
No!

11:40.280 --> 11:41.780
Terrible.
Well, Fonz,
you know,

11:41.780 --> 11:43.790
I'd drive, but
I'm hurt, too.
Yeah.

11:43.790 --> 11:44.790
(all groaning)
I am, I'm
hurt, look.

11:44.790 --> 11:45.790
All right,
all right, all right.

11:45.790 --> 11:47.290
Listen, I got
to think this out.

11:47.290 --> 11:48.120
Everybody just
get out of here.

11:48.410 --> 11:48.990
Come on, Shortcake, get out.

11:51.490 --> 11:53.000
Oh, Fonz, I'm sorry.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.330
Yeah, now I got to find
a substitute driver.

11:56.630 --> 11:58.130
I happen to know
the perfect person--

11:58.130 --> 11:59.890
Pinky Tuscadero.

12:00.090 --> 12:01.170
Hey, that's very nice.

12:01.170 --> 12:02.670
I'm low, you're
making a nice joke.

12:03.170 --> 12:04.010
That's very nice.

12:04.260 --> 12:05.810
What kind of joke?
This is my shot

12:05.810 --> 12:07.640
to be the first woman
in the derby.

12:07.890 --> 12:08.980
A woman in the derby?

12:08.980 --> 12:12.850
I got a problem, and you're
giving me silly suggestions.

12:15.770 --> 12:17.770
Ralph, you're driving with me.

12:17.770 --> 12:19.270
What?!
ALL:
Yay!

12:19.770 --> 12:21.270
No yay. No, no yay.

12:21.270 --> 12:23.280
Fonz, Fonz, I can't drive.
I'm hurt.

12:23.280 --> 12:24.780
Now, listen,
you're faking it.

12:24.780 --> 12:26.280
I'm going
to make you famous.

12:26.780 --> 12:28.280
Well, then, I'll hurt
myself, I promise.

12:28.280 --> 12:29.280
Somebody, hurt me!

12:29.280 --> 12:30.780
All right, all right,
look, I tell you,

12:31.280 --> 12:33.290
you're going to drive with me,
and that is it!

12:33.290 --> 12:35.290
Now stop babbling, make
some music for me, will you?

12:35.290 --> 12:36.290
All right.

12:36.290 --> 12:38.790
It's okay, Ralph.
It's okay.

12:38.790 --> 12:40.790
Dance.

12:42.800 --> 12:43.880
Hey, why don't you dance
with Ralph?

12:43.880 --> 12:44.760
He's your partner.

12:45.130 --> 12:47.130
Pinkettes, split!

12:47.470 --> 12:49.050
Ralph?

12:49.550 --> 12:51.050
Ralph is clumsy!

12:55.440 --> 12:58.030
You know, it's too bad
you two had to split up.

12:58.030 --> 12:59.530
Joanie.

12:59.530 --> 13:00.950
I hope you like
tapioca, Pinky.

13:01.310 --> 13:02.400
Oh, I love tapioca.

13:02.400 --> 13:04.700
I haven't seen that
since I was at the convent.

13:04.900 --> 13:05.480
The convent?

13:05.900 --> 13:06.820
Yeah.

13:09.160 --> 13:09.960
Were you a nun?

13:10.210 --> 13:11.620
Did they make you shave
your head?

13:11.870 --> 13:15.460
That's not
a polite question.

13:15.460 --> 13:17.410
Did they?

13:17.750 --> 13:19.830
I wasn't a nun.

13:19.830 --> 13:20.800
I just lived there.

13:21.170 --> 13:23.250
Well, how come you
lived in a convent?

13:23.250 --> 13:25.250
Now, this all might be
private, dear.

13:25.250 --> 13:28.140
I'd like to know,
too, Marion.

13:28.420 --> 13:29.510
It's not so private.

13:29.510 --> 13:32.510
You know, my mother and father
split up when I was a kid.

13:32.510 --> 13:34.010
You know, D-I-V-0-R-C-E.

13:34.430 --> 13:35.010
Divorce.

13:37.680 --> 13:38.770
Well, my mother
couldn't handle it,

13:38.770 --> 13:40.600
so she dropped me off
at the sisters'.

13:40.900 --> 13:41.990
Oh, that's too bad.

13:42.350 --> 13:43.940
Nah. Are you kidding?
I loved it.

13:43.940 --> 13:46.440
But 18 years old, either
you become a nun, or you leave.

13:46.440 --> 13:48.240
You know, split.
(whistles)

13:48.490 --> 13:52.030
It's just amazing how much
you and Fonzie have in common.

13:52.360 --> 13:54.280
Ah, forget it-- he wouldn't
even let me in the derby.

13:54.530 --> 13:56.120
But you <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">are
in the derby{\r}.</font></font></i>

13:56.120 --> 13:57.620
I mean, you're
the guest star.

13:57.620 --> 13:59.120
You're-You're
leading off the show

13:59.120 --> 14:00.460
with your
motorcycle tricks.

14:00.710 --> 14:02.090
Not as a driver.

14:02.420 --> 14:03.510
RICHIE:
Hi, folks. We're home.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.880
Oh, you're just in time
for dessert.

14:08.260 --> 14:09.770
Tapioca.

14:09.770 --> 14:11.770
We'll give you
some ice cream.

14:13.270 --> 14:14.770
Dad, uh...
Hmm?

14:14.770 --> 14:16.770
Will you come upstairs
with me for a minute?

14:16.770 --> 14:18.270
I haven't finished
my dessert yet.

14:18.770 --> 14:20.280
Well, you can finish it
upstairs, Dad.

14:20.280 --> 14:21.280
What are you doing?

14:21.780 --> 14:23.280
Well, we have
to talk.
Talk about what?

14:23.280 --> 14:25.280
I-I don't know.
The birds and the bees.

14:25.280 --> 14:27.280
Oh, Richard, we
already had that talk.

14:27.280 --> 14:29.290
Yeah, and you didn't
learn much.

14:31.450 --> 14:33.040
See, uh...

14:41.710 --> 14:45.130
There, uh, seems to be a little
tension between us here.

14:45.470 --> 14:47.970
Oh, you noticed?

14:48.300 --> 14:49.890
I had a long talk

14:49.890 --> 14:52.390
with Richie about
our misunderstanding.

14:52.390 --> 14:54.760
What did the
announcer say?

14:55.060 --> 14:58.650
Well, in between
his "huh-huh-huh's"

14:58.650 --> 15:00.650
he said that he thinks

15:00.650 --> 15:02.650
I should let you drive
in the derby, or you're going

15:02.650 --> 15:04.940
to get into a huff,
and you're going to walk out.

15:05.100 --> 15:07.490
You know,
redheads are just born geniuses.

15:07.690 --> 15:09.280
On the other hand,

15:09.740 --> 15:11.780
I don't think
you should be in the derby.

15:11.780 --> 15:13.280
I have spoken.

15:13.280 --> 15:15.280
That's that.

15:26.130 --> 15:29.710
You know, you got
the prettiest eyes.

15:34.720 --> 15:36.220
Come on now.

15:36.220 --> 15:38.220
I don't want any more
fighting here, all right?

15:38.220 --> 15:39.720
Come on.

15:39.720 --> 15:41.220
All right,
all right.
Hmm? Hmm?

15:41.220 --> 15:42.560
You got it, you got it.

15:42.810 --> 15:44.890
I still think
you're wrong, though.

15:44.890 --> 15:47.860
Why am I...
(shuddering)

15:53.240 --> 15:55.700
Is Ralph a better driver
than me?

15:55.960 --> 15:57.870
Ralph can't find reverse.

15:58.160 --> 16:00.740
You think when the action starts

16:00.740 --> 16:02.240
that I will panic
under pressure?

16:02.630 --> 16:04.960
Hey, Pinky, you know
I know that you're cool.

16:05.250 --> 16:07.670
Then give me one good reason
why I'm not your partner.

16:07.920 --> 16:09.000
The Lone Ranger.

16:09.000 --> 16:10.800
Was Tonto a girl?

16:11.050 --> 16:12.640
Oh, I don't know.

16:13.140 --> 16:14.510
He wore a feather.

16:14.760 --> 16:15.840
Hey, don't you joke

16:15.840 --> 16:18.340
about Tonto!

16:18.340 --> 16:19.350
I'm telling you something.

16:19.850 --> 16:21.760
There are always two guys--
that's right.

16:22.060 --> 16:25.150
Batman and Robin,
uh, the Green Hornet and Kato,

16:25.150 --> 16:28.020
Even Gene Autry had
a boy horse-- Champion!

16:29.910 --> 16:31.270
Roy Rogers and Dale Evans!

16:31.570 --> 16:33.660
Singers!
You're giving me singers!

16:34.160 --> 16:36.950
I'm talking about adventurers,
I'm talking about heroes,

16:37.160 --> 16:38.250
I'm talking about men

16:38.250 --> 16:40.120
that made this country
what it is today!

16:40.450 --> 16:42.030
Do you think that I, the Fonz,

16:42.030 --> 16:44.870
can break the tradition
by putting a woman in a derby?

16:45.090 --> 16:46.170
You know what I'm saying?

16:46.170 --> 16:47.670
Do you know
what I'm saying?

16:47.670 --> 16:49.680
No, I do not know
what you're saying!

16:49.680 --> 16:51.180
That's because pink
is fuzzing your brain!

16:51.680 --> 16:53.180
Yeah, I ought
to have it examined

16:53.180 --> 16:54.550
for hanging around
with you, boy!

16:54.880 --> 16:56.470
Ooh! Women!

17:03.970 --> 17:05.470
♪ I was moving
and a-groovin'-- whoo! ♪

17:05.970 --> 17:07.980
♪ We was a-reelin'
with the feelin' ♪

17:08.390 --> 17:10.480
♪ Hah! We was a-rollin'
and a-strollin' ♪

17:10.480 --> 17:12.480
♪ Movin' with the groovin' ♪

17:12.480 --> 17:13.480
♪ Splish, splash ♪

17:13.950 --> 17:14.980
♪ Yeah! ♪

17:14.980 --> 17:16.990
(cheering and applause)

17:20.990 --> 17:22.290
Thanks, Pinky.

17:22.540 --> 17:24.630
Hey, next time let's
try a fast number, huh?

17:24.630 --> 17:26.630
Yeah.

17:28.130 --> 17:29.000
RALPH:
Richie?

17:29.300 --> 17:30.380
Rich!
Hi, Ralph.

17:30.380 --> 17:31.880
How's your neck?
Better.
Listen to me.

17:31.880 --> 17:33.390
I just saw the Mallachi
brothers outside.

17:33.390 --> 17:34.390
The Mallachi brothers?

17:34.390 --> 17:35.390
Hey, they're
great drivers.

17:35.390 --> 17:37.170
They're favored to win
the derby, you know.

17:37.340 --> 17:38.420
You don't seem to understand.

17:38.420 --> 17:39.730
I'm in big danger.

17:39.930 --> 17:41.390
I know, they're mean.

17:41.890 --> 17:43.400
Hey, we ought to get
an interview with them.

17:43.400 --> 17:45.400
The public loves violence.
Richie, you're not
listening to me.

17:45.400 --> 17:46.350
Those guys might hurt me.

17:46.770 --> 17:48.350
Oh, look at this.
This is wild.

17:48.350 --> 17:51.850
One time in Cicero, the
Mallachis destroyed 27 cars

17:51.850 --> 17:53.360
with the famous
Mallachi Crunch.

17:53.360 --> 17:56.780
Only half the cars were
actually in the derby.

17:57.160 --> 17:59.240
I know-- I know
all about it.

17:59.240 --> 18:02.080
They're outside wrecking cars
in the parking lot right now.

18:02.280 --> 18:03.780
Oh, it's Rocco Mallachi!

18:04.170 --> 18:06.750
It's Rocco
Mallachi!

18:06.750 --> 18:08.250
Hello, Roc.

18:08.250 --> 18:09.250
Hello.

18:09.670 --> 18:14.210
Well, will the owner of the car,
license plate number

18:14.210 --> 18:17.180
B-4-9-3-6 please
raise your hand?

18:19.050 --> 18:21.050
Your lights are on.

18:23.050 --> 18:24.550
That could have
been my face!

18:25.940 --> 18:27.520
Uh, Rocco? Rocco Mallachi?

18:27.520 --> 18:29.530
I'm Richie Cunningham
from WZAZ-TV, and, uh...

18:30.030 --> 18:32.530
and we'd like to do a
little interview with you.

18:32.530 --> 18:34.030
Oh, yeah, uh,
just wait a second.

18:34.030 --> 18:36.030
Wait for my brother to
come, Count Mallachi.

18:36.030 --> 18:38.030
Hey, Count Mallachi,
come on in here.

18:38.030 --> 18:39.030
Count Mallachi?

18:39.490 --> 18:41.040
Yeah, he likes to be
called Count Mallachi.

18:41.540 --> 18:43.370
He thinks he's the Gorgeous
George of demolition derbies.

18:45.740 --> 18:47.740
I have arrived.

18:47.740 --> 18:49.550
Let the pigeons loose!

18:49.750 --> 18:52.330
Sorry, Count,
we're out of pigeons.

18:52.330 --> 18:55.630
How about some turkey
or chicken salad?

18:55.800 --> 18:58.300
You think I'm funny,
pickle nose?

18:58.590 --> 19:01.010
No. Have a free slice
of pizza.

19:03.810 --> 19:06.260
Or better yet, take it all.

19:06.650 --> 19:07.730
Let me ask you something.

19:07.730 --> 19:09.230
Why does he talk like that?

19:09.230 --> 19:10.730
Not that there's anything
wrong with it.

19:10.730 --> 19:13.150
He hasn't been the same since
he saw <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">The Three Musketeers{\r}.</font></font></i>

19:13.520 --> 19:16.570
Oh, lo and behold.

19:16.570 --> 19:19.610
It is the fair Pinky
of the derriere.

19:19.610 --> 19:22.110
Attend to me, fair maiden,
and I will sing to thee

19:22.610 --> 19:24.610
from my book
of songs and sonnets.

19:25.000 --> 19:27.000
Hey, why don't you go
sing into a bucket?

19:27.330 --> 19:28.420
(laughs)

19:28.420 --> 19:31.340
Clever, but very dangerous.

19:34.790 --> 19:35.790
MAN:
Hi, Fonz!

19:35.790 --> 19:37.180
WOMAN 2:
Here comes Fonzie!

19:37.540 --> 19:38.630
WOMAN:
Hi, Fonzie.

19:38.630 --> 19:40.960
Hey, Count, did
you say sonnets?

19:41.210 --> 19:42.800
Attend to me, maiden.

19:42.800 --> 19:45.300
Sit thee down
upon my fair knee.

19:46.800 --> 19:48.190
RICHIE:
All right,

19:48.470 --> 19:49.560
we're on the air.

19:49.560 --> 19:50.560
We're live at Arnold's,

19:50.560 --> 19:52.060
and we're expecting an interview

19:52.060 --> 19:54.060
with Arthur Fonzarelli
at any moment now.

19:54.060 --> 19:55.060
Here comes Fonzie.

19:55.560 --> 19:56.980
Fonz, I'd like...

19:59.150 --> 20:00.730
Bad time for an
interview, folks.

20:02.200 --> 20:03.740
Hey Fonz, Fonz,
I found a guy.

20:03.740 --> 20:05.740
He wants to drive
with you.

20:05.740 --> 20:07.710
Not now, Malph, not now.

20:10.910 --> 20:15.410
Ah, comrade, it has
been a long time, huh?

20:15.410 --> 20:17.420
Not long enough, Myron.

20:17.420 --> 20:19.170
He don't like you
to call him that.

20:19.380 --> 20:21.340
Well, let <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Myron tell me that
himself{\r}.</font></font></i>

20:21.670 --> 20:24.060
Ah, tush, an exception
for an old friend.

20:24.220 --> 20:25.090
Mm.

20:25.340 --> 20:27.930
Do I detect a note of
ill will in the air?

20:27.930 --> 20:29.930
Uh, someone in this room
does not think

20:30.430 --> 20:32.930
that I am good enough
to drive in the derby.

20:32.930 --> 20:36.690
Fiddle-ee-dee, thou
shall drive with me.

20:36.900 --> 20:38.490
If he keeps kissing your arm
like that,

20:38.990 --> 20:41.360
you're going to have
to get a shot for rabies.

20:47.830 --> 20:49.830
I'll ride with you, Count.

20:49.830 --> 20:50.830
'Tis settled then.

20:51.330 --> 20:52.280
Rocco, you're out.

20:52.700 --> 20:53.790
I-I'm your brother.

20:53.790 --> 20:55.290
I'll tell Mom.

20:55.290 --> 20:56.620
We're musketeers!

20:56.870 --> 20:58.960
You look more
like mouseketeers to me.

20:58.960 --> 21:01.930
With the little ears
and everything.

21:02.290 --> 21:03.880
Don't push it, Fonz.

21:03.880 --> 21:06.350
'Tis better to keep a
civil tongue in thy head.

21:06.680 --> 21:10.270
You know, Myron...
you're a clown.

21:20.450 --> 21:23.230
Rocco.

21:23.450 --> 21:25.030
Excuse me.

21:31.990 --> 21:33.580
(slow rock and roll
melody plays on jukebox)

21:33.580 --> 21:35.080
Dance, Count?

21:35.080 --> 21:37.410
I hear minstrels.

21:44.920 --> 21:46.510
It's the night
before the derby.

21:46.510 --> 21:48.840
Most of the combatants are
out on the dance floor.

21:49.090 --> 21:51.180
It's like the calm
before the storm.

21:53.180 --> 21:54.180
(music stops)

21:54.180 --> 21:55.680
This could be the storm.

21:57.680 --> 21:58.680
All right, listen up.

21:58.680 --> 22:00.520
There is an
announcement here.

22:00.740 --> 22:03.820
The itinerary
of drivers has been changed.

22:03.820 --> 22:06.110
Pinky, you drive with me.

22:06.330 --> 22:08.410
(crowd cheering and applauding)

22:09.860 --> 22:11.750
Oh, thank you, Lord, thank you.

22:14.580 --> 22:16.590
(music resumes)

22:21.670 --> 22:23.590
No more jokes about Tonto.

22:23.840 --> 22:25.760
Never.

22:29.100 --> 22:32.050
You have just witnessed
an historic moment.

22:32.470 --> 22:34.050
Pinky Tuscadero has been named

22:34.050 --> 22:36.560
to be the first woman driver
in the Demolition Derby.

22:37.060 --> 22:39.560
We'll talk to her now
and see how she feels.

22:42.060 --> 22:43.980
We'll interview that
history-making couple later.

23:03.470 --> 23:05.250
♪ A sweetheart ♪

23:05.470 --> 23:08.550
♪ Sends a letter ♪

23:08.970 --> 23:10.970
♪ Of good-bye... ♪

23:11.310 --> 23:12.890
It's getting late.

23:13.390 --> 23:14.680
What do you want
to do now?

23:14.890 --> 23:16.930
♪ It's no secret... ♪

23:20.350 --> 23:21.820
All right.

23:22.100 --> 23:25.100
Yeah, but first we've gotta give
Cunningham his interview, huh?

23:25.490 --> 23:27.070
(sighs)

23:27.070 --> 23:29.070
Oh great, all right,
okay.

23:29.070 --> 23:30.080
Let's go,
come on, guys.

23:30.080 --> 23:31.580
Come on, get the camera
in position, okay?

23:32.080 --> 23:33.080
All right.

23:33.080 --> 23:34.080
Come on.

23:34.080 --> 23:36.080
Get over here.

23:36.080 --> 23:38.080
Okay.

23:38.080 --> 23:40.090
All right.

23:40.090 --> 23:42.590
This is Richie Cunningham
in an exclusive interview

23:42.590 --> 23:45.090
with Arthur Fonzarelli
and Pinky Tuscadero,

23:45.590 --> 23:47.090
and I got it
for you, boy.

23:47.090 --> 23:49.540
I stayed up all night
for this thing.

23:49.880 --> 23:51.460
Uh, tell me, Fonzie,

23:51.460 --> 23:53.470
aren't you concerned about
the Mallachi brothers?

23:53.470 --> 23:54.470
They have a reputation

23:54.470 --> 23:56.270
for being unscrupulous
and devious.

23:56.520 --> 23:58.520
Hey, I don't know about that;
I just know they cheat.

23:58.800 --> 24:01.390
Well, uh, aren't
you worried

24:01.390 --> 24:03.390
that the Mallachi
brothers will try
and do something

24:03.390 --> 24:04.780
to keep you out
of the derby?

24:05.060 --> 24:07.650
Yeah, so I'm taking precautions.

24:08.150 --> 24:10.650
I got my car at your house
being guarded by your parents,

24:10.650 --> 24:13.650
and this lovely young lady's car
is at my garage,

24:13.650 --> 24:16.660
being guarded by two very
good personal friends.

24:18.160 --> 24:20.660
Hey, if Pinky
retires...

24:20.660 --> 24:22.160
Yeah?
I could
become the star

24:22.160 --> 24:23.660
and we'll get you
another Pinkette.

24:23.660 --> 24:25.160
Why you?
Well, red hair.

24:25.160 --> 24:26.670
Yeah, they're gonna
call you Reddy?

24:26.670 --> 24:28.670
Hi, girls!

24:28.670 --> 24:30.170
Look at this.
Whoa!
Call Fonzie!

24:30.170 --> 24:31.670
Yeah.
Oh, why call him?

24:31.670 --> 24:32.670
You'll see him
at the party.

24:33.170 --> 24:34.170
What party?
Are you sure?

24:34.170 --> 24:35.670
Oh, it's a--
it's a big party!

24:35.670 --> 24:37.560
It needs your sparkling
personalities.

24:37.840 --> 24:39.430
Oh!
Fonzie sent me
to get you.

24:39.930 --> 24:41.930
Yeah, yeah!
(giggling)

25:06.760 --> 25:08.760
Look, Alfred, just send
Fonzie over here

25:08.760 --> 25:10.040
as soon as you
see him,

25:10.290 --> 25:11.380
all right?

25:11.380 --> 25:13.380
Yeah, well-well somebody wrecked
Pinky's car--

25:13.380 --> 25:15.380
smashed up the whole engine.

25:15.380 --> 25:16.380
I think it was the Mallachis.

25:16.800 --> 25:18.380
RICHIE:
They painted a
big red "M"

25:18.380 --> 25:20.220
on the side
of the car.

25:20.470 --> 25:22.550
No, no, don't tell Fonzie that.

25:23.050 --> 25:24.560
No, just-just send him
over here.

25:24.970 --> 25:26.060
Okay.

25:26.060 --> 25:28.060
We've gotta keep
Fonzie calm.
Calm?

25:28.060 --> 25:29.530
He's gonna come in here
and go berserk!

25:29.860 --> 25:30.950
Gotta use
psychology.

25:30.950 --> 25:32.950
Very tricky
psychology.

25:32.950 --> 25:34.950
(tires squealing,
engine rumbling)

25:34.950 --> 25:35.950
Oh no,
that's Fonzie!

25:35.950 --> 25:37.450
Okay, now
what do we do, Rich?

25:37.450 --> 25:39.290
We shove all this stuff
under the hood!

25:40.620 --> 25:42.120
That's psychology?

25:42.620 --> 25:45.130
You let me do all
the talking with Fonzie.

25:45.630 --> 25:48.080
I've handled him all the other
times he's been upset.

25:48.080 --> 25:49.630
All right, you do
all the talking.

25:49.630 --> 25:50.630
All right, yeah,
put that down,

25:50.630 --> 25:52.130
put the hood down Ralph,
come on,

25:52.130 --> 25:53.130
and just act natural,
all right?

25:53.640 --> 25:54.640
Just act nat...

25:54.640 --> 25:56.640
Holding a fan is
not acting natural!

25:56.640 --> 25:57.590
Oh, my gosh!

26:00.060 --> 26:01.560
Lads, lads, lads.

26:02.060 --> 26:03.060
Oh, hi, Fonz.

26:03.560 --> 26:04.560
How are you?

26:04.560 --> 26:06.570
Great day for the derby,
huh, Fonz?

26:06.570 --> 26:08.570
Fonzie's here,
Ralph.

26:08.570 --> 26:10.570
Hi, Fonz.
You're here.

26:10.570 --> 26:12.850
Beautiful day,
huh, Fonz?

26:13.020 --> 26:14.610
Yeah, it's a beautiful day

26:15.110 --> 26:18.030
for anything
and <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">everything, eh{\r}?</font></font></i>

26:18.360 --> 26:19.910
Anything.
Right, everything.
Anything.

26:20.280 --> 26:21.750
Listen, now, I'm gonna get
in that car, right?

26:22.030 --> 26:23.620
So get out of the way, I want
to warm up the engine.

26:23.620 --> 26:24.370
RICHIE:
There's something I gotta
tell you, Fonz.

26:24.620 --> 26:26.200
Uh...

26:26.700 --> 26:29.170
Fonze, uh, something
unexpected has happened, see?

26:29.170 --> 26:31.210
And it's important that
you keep an open mind.

26:31.710 --> 26:33.210
Do you believe
in destiny?

26:33.710 --> 26:36.210
Is this gonna
be a religious talk?

26:36.210 --> 26:37.210
It's not a
religious talk.

26:37.630 --> 26:39.210
Hey, hey, hey, this
is not funny here.

26:39.210 --> 26:40.100
This car don't start.

26:40.380 --> 26:41.470
Well, just remember:

26:41.970 --> 26:43.270
"To forgive is divine."

26:43.470 --> 26:44.550
Sorry, Pinky.
We're sorry.

26:44.550 --> 26:46.050
We're sorry.
We're sorry.

26:46.050 --> 26:48.060
My two aces are blowing it.

26:48.060 --> 26:49.560
They're going to a party
with Rocco

26:49.560 --> 26:50.560
instead of guarding my car.

26:50.980 --> 26:52.560
What's wrong with
this, Pink?

26:52.560 --> 26:53.560
It doesn't start.
Hey, Fonze, don't...

26:53.560 --> 26:55.560
don't look under
that hood, okay?
No. No.

26:55.560 --> 26:56.480
Get off that hood!

26:56.870 --> 26:57.950
Don't look
under there.

26:57.950 --> 26:58.950
No! No!

26:58.950 --> 27:02.040
(all shouting at once)

27:03.370 --> 27:04.870
Hey!

27:07.960 --> 27:10.550
All right, now we all
saw what just happened...

27:11.050 --> 27:13.550
and, uh, I know exactly
what to do.

27:16.050 --> 27:17.590
All right, Malph,
get over here.

27:18.090 --> 27:19.090
I want you and Potsie

27:19.090 --> 27:20.510
to get me a gallon
of pink paint.

27:20.840 --> 27:22.420
RALPH: Right, Fonz.
POTSIE:
Right, Fonz.

27:22.420 --> 27:24.430
All right, Tina, Lola,
get over here.

27:24.430 --> 27:25.930
All right now, listen--

27:25.930 --> 27:27.430
I want you to go
to Pfister's Emporium,

27:27.430 --> 27:29.430
I want you to get me a tire,
standard size;

27:29.430 --> 27:31.430
I want you to get me points
and plugs, dig it?

27:31.430 --> 27:32.770
Oh, we're sorry,
Fonz, really.

27:33.020 --> 27:34.100
Are you mad at us?

27:34.100 --> 27:35.100
Well, what you did
was wrong,

27:35.100 --> 27:36.910
but like they say,
to forgive is what?

27:37.110 --> 27:38.690
Divine.
Divine!

27:38.690 --> 27:40.190
Thank you.

27:40.190 --> 27:41.190
All right, Richie,
get over here.
Right.

27:41.190 --> 27:42.690
I want you
to tell your father

27:42.690 --> 27:45.500
to stall the beginning of the
derby for as long as he can.

27:45.700 --> 27:47.200
Yeah, well, I'm gonna get him
to disqualify the Mallachis.

27:47.530 --> 27:49.120
No, don't disqualify 'em.

27:49.620 --> 27:51.120
I'm gonna take care
of 'em in the derby.

27:51.500 --> 27:53.590
Fonz, I don't know if
I can leave you at
a time like this.

27:53.590 --> 27:55.590
Like what?
Well, you're obviously
very upset.

27:55.590 --> 27:57.540
They wrecked the car--
I'm afraid you're
gonna go out there,

27:57.880 --> 27:58.960
try and get revenge...
Richie!

27:58.960 --> 28:01.260
I'm gonna be just fine,
will you get out of here?

28:01.460 --> 28:03.050
Fonz, I am proud of you.

28:03.550 --> 28:05.050
It is amazing how
calm you are

28:05.050 --> 28:06.520
under these
circumstances.
Hey, Richie...

28:06.850 --> 28:09.440
Richie, I asked your father
to stall, not you.

28:09.440 --> 28:10.940
Oh, you want
me to go?
Yeah.

28:10.940 --> 28:12.440
I'm going, Fonz.

28:15.440 --> 28:17.450
You think you can fix this
in time for the derby?

28:17.950 --> 28:19.450
I'll fix it.

28:19.950 --> 28:21.450
Pretty Eyes,
you're amazing.

28:21.450 --> 28:22.450
No man alive

28:22.950 --> 28:23.950
could have handled
a disaster like this.

28:23.950 --> 28:24.950
You know something?

28:25.370 --> 28:26.400
You are the coolest.

28:26.790 --> 28:28.370
Yeah.
The coolest.

28:28.370 --> 28:31.160
Yeah, I know, man, I...

28:31.410 --> 28:32.490
I am cool.

28:32.490 --> 28:35.130
But I'm losing it!

28:35.410 --> 28:37.000
Wait!

28:46.010 --> 28:48.010
I got it back.

28:50.850 --> 28:51.850
HOWARD:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Stall{\r}?</font></font></i>

28:51.850 --> 28:52.760
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">That's impossible{\r}.</font></font></i>

28:53.060 --> 28:54.650
Absolutely
impossible, Richard.

28:54.650 --> 28:56.650
Do you know what
you're asking of me?

28:56.650 --> 28:58.150
Dad, you have
to stall.

28:58.150 --> 29:00.660
Look, do you want to have
a derby with no Fonzie?

29:00.660 --> 29:03.160
You're asking me,
an unarmed man,

29:03.160 --> 29:05.660
to get up in front of that
Demolition Derby crowd,

29:05.660 --> 29:08.160
people who have probably
eaten raw meat for breakfast,

29:08.160 --> 29:10.670
and say "Sorry, we have
to delay the derby."

29:10.670 --> 29:12.000
Is that the way
you picture it?

29:12.280 --> 29:13.870
Well, I thought
you'd start off

29:13.870 --> 29:14.790
by telling a few jokes.

29:15.170 --> 29:16.760
Oh, that's a good idea.

29:17.260 --> 29:18.760
Yeah, jokes are good.
Yeah.

29:18.760 --> 29:20.760
How about this one?

29:20.760 --> 29:24.710
How did the moron get involved
with the Demolition Derby?

29:25.210 --> 29:26.630
I don't know, Dad. How?

29:27.020 --> 29:28.880
His son talked him into it.

29:30.190 --> 29:32.140
I never heard that one.

29:32.470 --> 29:35.060
Richard, this is
all your fault.

29:37.060 --> 29:39.060
The Leopards should have had
a picnic, just like always.

29:39.560 --> 29:41.030
Now, that's fun stuff!

29:41.030 --> 29:43.450
We had softball games
and sack races.

29:43.700 --> 29:45.280
You remember the time
your mother sat

29:45.280 --> 29:46.790
in the potato salad, huh?

29:46.790 --> 29:48.150
That's fun stuff!

29:48.490 --> 29:50.570
Dad, those are
bygone days.

29:51.070 --> 29:52.570
Now, come on, are you
gonna stall or not?

29:52.990 --> 29:55.080
Well, okay, I guess
I've got no choice.

29:55.080 --> 29:56.580
Oh, great.
I'll try to stall.

29:57.080 --> 29:58.580
I just hope my insurance
is paid up.

29:59.080 --> 30:00.580
Well, we'll all
help you stall.

30:01.080 --> 30:03.050
I'll lengthen
my starter speech.

30:03.420 --> 30:06.000
Marion, all you're
gonna say is,

30:06.000 --> 30:08.010
"Gentlemen,
start your engines."

30:08.010 --> 30:09.310
I'll stutter.

30:11.890 --> 30:13.340
Why are you bringing
a hair dryer?

30:13.600 --> 30:14.680
Fonzie asked for it.

30:14.680 --> 30:16.510
He said he'd need it
against the Mallachis.

30:16.730 --> 30:18.320
Well, I knew they
were mean,

30:18.320 --> 30:20.600
but I didn't think they'd
mess up people's hair.

30:22.900 --> 30:24.410
I'm gonna have to get over
to the field.

30:24.410 --> 30:25.410
But, Dad, listen,

30:25.410 --> 30:27.190
I think you should
tell a few jokes.

30:27.360 --> 30:28.440
Uh, especially that one

30:28.440 --> 30:29.940
about the nearsighted
ostrich with the hat.

30:29.940 --> 30:32.450
That one always
knocks 'em dead.

30:32.450 --> 30:34.450
Richard...
Yeah?

30:34.450 --> 30:35.950
Go to the field...
Uh-huh?

30:35.950 --> 30:37.950
and sit on it.

30:44.340 --> 30:46.430
What, the nearsighted
ostrich with the hat?

30:46.430 --> 30:47.300
I don't know that one.

30:47.550 --> 30:49.930
You never will, dear,
it's a smut joke.

30:50.130 --> 30:52.720
Mom, I'll tell you
in the car.

30:53.220 --> 30:54.720
You'll love it!
You'll love it!

30:57.220 --> 31:00.530
POTSIE:
♪ O, beautiful
for spacious skies ♪

31:00.730 --> 31:04.730
♪ For amber waves of grain ♪

31:05.060 --> 31:09.200
♪ For purple mountains'
majesty ♪

31:09.400 --> 31:10.490
(feedback squeals)

31:10.490 --> 31:13.400
♪ Above the fruited plain ♪

31:13.740 --> 31:17.960
♪ America, America ♪

31:18.160 --> 31:21.080
♪ God shed his grace on thee ♪

31:21.380 --> 31:25.800
♪ And crown thy good
with brotherhood ♪

31:26.170 --> 31:31.170
♪ From sea to shining sea. ♪

31:31.670 --> 31:33.060
(cheering and applause)

31:33.340 --> 31:35.810
That was Potsie Weber
with "America the Beautiful."

31:36.090 --> 31:37.480
(cheering, whistling
and applause)

31:37.730 --> 31:39.310
Hey, hey, who's gonna
have some pizza?

31:39.310 --> 31:40.820
Come on folks,
be happy, be happy.

31:41.230 --> 31:42.320
The Pinkettes
have performed

31:42.320 --> 31:43.820
for 20 minutes longer
than they were supposed to,

31:43.820 --> 31:44.820
now what am I gonna do?

31:46.650 --> 31:48.240
You're gonna have to
think of something.

31:48.240 --> 31:50.240
You're the chairman.
All right, all right.

31:50.240 --> 31:51.240
I'll-I'll think
of something.

31:51.740 --> 31:52.740
I know what I'm
gonna do.

31:52.740 --> 31:54.080
Uh-uh, folks?

31:54.330 --> 31:56.410
We're gonna be ready to start
in-in just a few minutes.

31:56.920 --> 31:57.780
But first, uh,

31:58.080 --> 32:00.670
did you hear the one about
the nearsighted ostrich?

32:01.170 --> 32:02.670
Oh, Howard,
not that one.

32:02.670 --> 32:04.010
I'm desperate, Marion.

32:04.290 --> 32:05.870
Hey, sweetie,

32:05.870 --> 32:07.380
did you know
I'm a backup driver?

32:07.380 --> 32:10.380
I could be in the derby
any minute.

32:10.380 --> 32:13.300
So, I'll be your backup
boyfriend.

32:13.600 --> 32:15.180
Howard, you're gonna
be in big trouble

32:15.180 --> 32:16.680
if you don't stop drinking
all that soda.

32:16.680 --> 32:18.190
You get nervous
and excited,

32:18.190 --> 32:20.190
and you have to go to the
bathroom all the time.

32:20.190 --> 32:21.690
We're all gonna be
in big trouble, Marion,

32:21.690 --> 32:23.690
if Fonzie doesn't
show up pretty soon.

32:23.690 --> 32:26.140
Why do you say that?

32:26.480 --> 32:27.560
HOWARD:
That's why, Marion.

32:27.560 --> 32:28.360
ROCCO:
Hey, let's get started.

32:28.610 --> 32:30.700
Hey you, with the tiger
on your head.

32:30.700 --> 32:32.200
It's a leopard
on my head.

32:32.700 --> 32:34.950
A tiger, no problem.
Same jungle.

32:35.240 --> 32:37.160
I just know that Fonzie's
gonna show up.

32:37.460 --> 32:39.490
Give him five more minutes,
and then I'll... I'll
wave the flag.

32:39.490 --> 32:40.330
COUNT:
Press on, huh?

32:40.540 --> 32:42.460
Yeah, let's go, huh?

32:42.660 --> 32:43.750
HOWARD:
I'll be right
back, Marion.

32:44.160 --> 32:48.550
In the meantime,
you pray thee for me.

32:48.750 --> 32:52.300
RICHIE:
Over here is the spot
where Pinky would be

32:52.300 --> 32:53.840
if Pinky was here.

32:53.840 --> 32:55.840
And on this side of the ring,

32:55.840 --> 32:58.760
the spot where Fonzie
will be if he shows up.

32:59.140 --> 33:01.510
And on this side of the ring,
we have...

33:01.680 --> 33:03.260
(drumroll)
Boo Boo Fox...

33:03.260 --> 33:05.020
and next to him,
his partner,

33:05.520 --> 33:08.020
a local favorite,
Mad Man Mahocky.

33:08.020 --> 33:08.820
On the other side

33:09.020 --> 33:10.100
of the ring we have
Filthy Marvin

33:10.100 --> 33:12.020
and his partner,
No Nose Quirk.

33:12.520 --> 33:14.360
Good luck,
No Nose.

33:14.610 --> 33:15.690
(chuckles)

33:16.190 --> 33:17.700
No Nose, Boo Boo...

33:17.700 --> 33:19.700
makes me think
I got a dull name.

33:20.200 --> 33:22.120
But, th-that's a story
in itself.

33:22.450 --> 33:24.040
Hi, girls.

33:24.540 --> 33:26.040
I'm Ralph "the Flash" Malph.

33:26.540 --> 33:28.040
I'm a driver here
at the derby.

33:28.040 --> 33:29.510
I guess you're
pretty impressed.

33:31.930 --> 33:33.380
They don't understand drivers.

33:33.800 --> 33:36.630
And next, we have the diabolical
Count Mallachi,

33:36.850 --> 33:38.800
and his brother Rocco.

33:39.050 --> 33:40.470
(booing)

33:40.770 --> 33:42.350
Let the pigeons loose!

33:42.770 --> 33:44.140
We have no pigeons.

33:44.360 --> 33:46.860
RICHIE:
That's the end
of the introductions.

33:47.190 --> 33:49.280
While we're waiting for some
of the activities to begin,

33:49.780 --> 33:52.280
let's go over the rules
of team Demolition Derby.

33:52.730 --> 33:55.280
Each team is made up
of two cars

33:55.280 --> 33:57.290
and their,
and their drivers...

33:57.290 --> 33:59.790
uh, driving in
a marked, circled area.

33:59.790 --> 34:02.790
The object of the contest is
to slam into the others' cars

34:02.790 --> 34:04.790
until they're out of operation.

34:04.790 --> 34:07.300
The winner is the last car
that can still move.

34:07.300 --> 34:10.300
All drivers must wear
seat belts and helmets...

34:10.300 --> 34:11.250
(engine roaring,
tires squealing)

34:11.670 --> 34:13.500
(cheering)

34:13.719 --> 34:14.719
He's here! Fonzie's here!

34:15.050 --> 34:17.639
Yes, it's car number seven,
Pinky Tuscadero,

34:18.139 --> 34:20.639
and Arthur Fonzarelli
in car number six.

34:20.639 --> 34:23.639
He showed up, ladies and
gentlemen, just as I expected.

34:23.639 --> 34:26.100
Fonzie did it.
He fixed Pinky's car.

34:26.510 --> 34:27.600
Woo-hoo!

34:27.600 --> 34:29.100
Pinky, it goes
with your hair.

34:29.100 --> 34:30.440
Oh, it's just
beautiful!

34:41.750 --> 34:43.699
Hey, thanks for busting up
Pinky's car.

34:44.000 --> 34:46.080
Sir Fonzo
of the Milwaukee,

34:46.580 --> 34:49.090
and his lovely maiden
Pinky of the derriere.

34:49.090 --> 34:50.920
What's a derriere?
Trust me.

34:51.170 --> 34:52.670
Let's get on with this here.

34:52.960 --> 34:53.460
Adieu.

34:58.800 --> 34:59.880
Now, look, Marion,
are you sure

34:59.880 --> 35:01.380
you know what
you're gonna say?

35:01.380 --> 35:02.880
Course I do: Gentlemen,
start your engines.

35:02.880 --> 35:03.770
That's perfect.

35:04.050 --> 35:06.600
(applause, cheering)

35:10.020 --> 35:11.440
Hey, Myron, we're ready to go.

35:11.730 --> 35:13.310
Never let "Myron" pass thy lips,

35:13.310 --> 35:15.150
least my fist
shall smash thy face.

35:15.360 --> 35:16.730
Right-- Count. Count.

35:22.120 --> 35:23.540
Pinky, where is your helmet?

35:23.790 --> 35:25.320
I don't like a helmet.

35:25.320 --> 35:26.710
It's not me-- you know that.

35:26.910 --> 35:27.490
Let's go.

35:27.990 --> 35:29.490
Oh, that chick has got to learn.

35:29.490 --> 35:30.800
You got to learn.

35:31.080 --> 35:32.660
Now we'd like to take you
to the grandstand,

35:32.660 --> 35:34.670
where Howard Cunningham,
the chairman

35:34.670 --> 35:36.670
of the Leopard Lodge
Demolition Derby,

35:36.670 --> 35:38.670
is waiting to start
the big event.

35:38.670 --> 35:40.000
Howard?

35:40.220 --> 35:41.810
Ladies and gentlemen,

35:41.810 --> 35:43.810
here is your
lovely starter,

35:43.810 --> 35:45.180
Marion Cunningham.

35:45.480 --> 35:47.010
(cheering, whooping)

35:47.400 --> 35:49.480
(laughing nervously)

35:49.480 --> 35:50.980
Uh...

35:50.980 --> 35:54.490
Gentlemen,
start your junk!

35:55.770 --> 35:57.160
(echoing):
Oh, Howard...

35:57.360 --> 35:59.740
(engines starting)

36:00.020 --> 36:01.110
Count. I said Count.

36:01.580 --> 36:02.440
He can't remember Count?

36:05.830 --> 36:07.920
And now we're ready
for the derby to begin.

36:07.920 --> 36:09.920
We'll be right back
after this message.

36:16.290 --> 36:17.380
Oh, Howard, I'm sorry.

36:17.380 --> 36:18.880
Start your junk...
Marion...

36:18.880 --> 36:19.880
Well, you--
forget it.

36:19.880 --> 36:21.380
Just-just-just
wave the flag, huh?
Okay.

36:21.380 --> 36:23.760
Wave, wave...
No, no, Marion...

36:24.100 --> 36:26.100
Drop it!
I'm sorry.

36:26.470 --> 36:27.970
Let loose the pigeons.

36:28.350 --> 36:31.940
RICHIE:
With the drop of the flag,
the derby begins.

36:31.940 --> 36:32.940
(crashing, metal screeching)

36:33.360 --> 36:34.860
All right, Pinky,
that a girl, go get them!

36:35.190 --> 36:36.060
(whooping)

36:36.280 --> 36:37.780
(tires screeching)

36:39.980 --> 36:41.820
Not bad, not bad.

36:42.150 --> 36:43.650
Hey, Mom should see us now, huh?

36:43.990 --> 36:45.990
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Rocco is going for the Fonz{\r}.</font></font></i>

36:46.370 --> 36:48.240
Watch out, sweetheart.
(gasps)

36:48.570 --> 36:50.120
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Pinky intercepts the hit{\r}.</font></font></i>

36:50.490 --> 36:52.080
PINKY:
I took the hit
for you, Fonz.

36:52.080 --> 36:53.330
Why'd you do that, Pinky?

36:53.540 --> 36:54.910
I'd do anything for you,
you know that.

36:55.160 --> 36:57.050
That a girl, Pinky,
that's why I love you!

36:57.220 --> 36:58.300
You sure they
won't be hurt?

36:58.800 --> 36:59.800
Marion, they're
wearing helmets,

36:59.800 --> 37:01.300
and they got seat belts,

37:01.300 --> 37:02.800
and they wear
padded suits.

37:02.800 --> 37:04.310
As long as they stay
in the cars,

37:04.310 --> 37:05.560
they won't get hurt.

37:05.810 --> 37:07.760
Oh, boy, I'll tell you,
I'm in my element now.

37:08.180 --> 37:09.180
(crashing)

37:10.810 --> 37:12.850
I'm gonna get that guy,
the Fonz.

37:14.430 --> 37:15.430
(screaming)

37:15.770 --> 37:16.820
Oh, that was a bad one.

37:17.150 --> 37:20.190
How am I doing in my rear?
Tell me, how am I doing?

37:20.570 --> 37:21.660
Watch out!

37:21.660 --> 37:23.160
Wahoo!

37:23.160 --> 37:24.580
This is Pinky's day, honey.

37:24.940 --> 37:25.530
(groaning)

37:25.940 --> 37:28.410
(crashing,
tires screeching)

37:28.700 --> 37:30.030
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Fonzie to Filthy Marvin{\r}.</font></font></i>

37:30.280 --> 37:31.170
Come on, Pinky!

37:33.370 --> 37:35.450
And Pinky hits Lefty
a good jolt.

37:35.450 --> 37:36.950
She's a great driver,
ladies and gentlemen.

37:36.950 --> 37:37.870
She can do it all.

37:38.290 --> 37:39.870
Look at them go!
(laughs)

37:39.870 --> 37:41.760
Hey, come on.

37:44.210 --> 37:46.680
Oh, knave,
thou dare toucheth me?

37:46.930 --> 37:49.300
I'll touch you--
get outta here!

37:50.970 --> 37:52.890
(gasps)

37:53.140 --> 37:54.560
The Mallachi Crunch in reverse.

37:57.860 --> 38:00.440
Wow! You just saw it yourself,
ladies and gentlemen.

38:00.440 --> 38:02.450
That's the Mallachi Crunch.

38:02.450 --> 38:03.450
Now you know why they're known

38:03.450 --> 38:05.280
as the terrors
of the demolition derby.

38:05.480 --> 38:07.870
(tires screeching)
Look out, Count, it's the Fonz!

38:12.210 --> 38:13.570
Give 'em another
shot, Fonzie!

38:15.210 --> 38:16.880
(screaming, cheering)

38:19.160 --> 38:20.080
Whoa! Missed him on that one.

38:20.330 --> 38:21.250
(crowd shouting)

38:22.830 --> 38:23.720
Come on, let's go.

38:26.250 --> 38:28.060
All right, Count,
start counting.

38:28.310 --> 38:29.840
Well done, Sir Fonzie.

38:30.310 --> 38:31.840
(crashing)

38:31.840 --> 38:34.180
All right, we got 'em
huh, Pinky?

38:34.430 --> 38:36.730
(whoops)
The Mallachi Crunch coming up.

38:37.060 --> 38:38.520
Fonzie's car is stalled.

38:38.850 --> 38:41.350
The Mallachis are set up
for the Crunch.

38:41.740 --> 38:42.820
Yeah?

38:42.820 --> 38:43.820
(engine revving)

38:43.820 --> 38:45.660
And now I'm not stalled.

38:45.990 --> 38:47.580
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">He started the car{\r}.</font></font></i>

38:47.580 --> 38:50.080
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">He's moving, and he slips
through the Mallachi Crunch{\r}!</font></font></i>

38:50.080 --> 38:51.080
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">They've hit each other{\r}.</font></font></i>

38:51.500 --> 38:53.950
(laughing):
Fonzie escaped
the Mallachi Crunch.

38:54.280 --> 38:56.250
Boy, those nerds
never learn, huh?

38:56.620 --> 38:58.090
(crashing)

38:58.420 --> 39:00.420
(cars crashing, banging
loudly)

39:07.600 --> 39:08.550
(crowd screaming)

39:11.850 --> 39:13.800
(crashing)

39:14.100 --> 39:16.270
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">The Mallachis just took out
another car{\r}.</font></font></i>

39:16.600 --> 39:18.690
And with that crash,
flagman Potsie Weber

39:18.690 --> 39:21.190
is on the field,
waving his yellow flag.

39:21.190 --> 39:23.980
You remember Potsie-- he sang
"America The Beautiful."

39:24.200 --> 39:26.610
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">The yellow flag
signals all car{\r}s</font></font></i>

39:26.900 --> 39:28.820
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">to proceed with
extreme caution{\r}.</font></font></i>

39:29.120 --> 39:32.700
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">That's the third car
to be forced out of this derby{\r}.</font></font></i>

39:38.290 --> 39:39.660
(mouthing words)

39:41.660 --> 39:43.750
There are many fascinating
human interest stories

39:43.750 --> 39:46.250
which go on behind
the scenes at this derby.

39:46.250 --> 39:49.250
We'd like to talk to Alfred
of Arnold's Restaurant

39:49.250 --> 39:51.260
and see how he feels
about these delays.

39:51.260 --> 39:53.760
You're on the air.

39:53.760 --> 39:56.760
Hi, I'm Alfred
of Arnold's.

39:56.760 --> 39:59.260
And how do you feel
about these delays?

39:59.260 --> 40:01.770
Hi, I'm Alfred
of Arnold's.

40:04.070 --> 40:06.070
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">They've started up again,
and we're back to actio{\r}n</font></font></i>

40:06.070 --> 40:07.860
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">with only six cars left
in the derby{\r}.</font></font></i>

40:07.860 --> 40:10.320
It looks like Lefty Banducci
is stalled.

40:10.320 --> 40:12.860
ROCCO:
Here's some flour
for you, sonny.

40:12.860 --> 40:15.780
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">And Rocco throws flour
in his face{\r}!</font></font></i>

40:15.780 --> 40:16.950
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">And Lefty can't see{\r}.</font></font></i>

40:16.950 --> 40:18.030
Is that fair?

40:18.530 --> 40:20.920
In a demolition derby,
Marion, everything is fair.

40:20.920 --> 40:23.200
They gotta crunch again--
they are boring.

40:23.200 --> 40:24.460
(groaning)

40:28.460 --> 40:30.010
Come on, Fonzie, go!

40:30.010 --> 40:30.930
I'm going.

40:34.520 --> 40:35.630
Whoo!

40:35.630 --> 40:37.100
Whoa, what a hit.

40:38.600 --> 40:39.690
Rocco's going to try

40:39.690 --> 40:41.190
the flour trick on Fonzie.

40:41.190 --> 40:43.770
Fonzie, I have some fine flour
for you.

40:43.770 --> 40:45.690
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Rocco's throwing flour
at Fonzie{\r},</font></font></i>

40:45.690 --> 40:46.780
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">and Fonzie pulls out
a hair dryer{\r}.</font></font></i>

40:47.280 --> 40:48.110
That's not fair!

40:49.650 --> 40:51.070
Oh, you little devil.

40:51.070 --> 40:52.650
How about that,
ladies and gentlemen?

40:52.650 --> 40:55.320
Fonzie beat the Mallachis
at their own game.

40:55.320 --> 40:58.320
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Hey, Fonzie got them
with a hair dryer{\r}.</font></font></i>

41:00.120 --> 41:02.040
Wow!

41:02.040 --> 41:03.130
You told me we
were going to have

41:03.130 --> 41:04.960
a nice close-up place--
look how far we are.

41:07.470 --> 41:08.550
There it is, folks.

41:08.550 --> 41:09.970
We have another
break in the action.

41:09.970 --> 41:12.470
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">And there goes Potsie Weber
with his yellow flag{\r}.</font></font></i>

41:17.310 --> 41:19.510
ROCCO:
Let's shake up
that Potsie kid!

41:22.100 --> 41:24.270
(screaming)

41:24.270 --> 41:27.650
The flag goes up, and
the contest continues.

41:27.650 --> 41:31.110
(tires screeching)

41:31.110 --> 41:32.610
(whooping)

41:32.610 --> 41:33.490
Come on, Pinky!

41:36.330 --> 41:38.330
(tires squealing,
cars crashing)

41:40.280 --> 41:41.870
We're definitely too close!

41:41.870 --> 41:42.780
(yells)

41:44.170 --> 41:45.450
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">There are only two teams left{\r},</font></font></i>

41:45.450 --> 41:46.540
ladies and gentlemen.

41:46.540 --> 41:48.540
Fonzie and Pinky
are squaring off

41:48.540 --> 41:49.840
against the Mallachi brothers,

41:49.840 --> 41:51.430
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">and to come this far
in the derby{\r},</font></font></i>

41:51.430 --> 41:53.430
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">you know these drivers have
to be good{\r}.</font></font></i>

41:53.930 --> 41:55.260
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">They have to be able to charg{\r}e</font></font></i>

41:55.260 --> 41:58.050
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">and hit with their backs while
they protect their engines{\r}.</font></font></i>

41:58.050 --> 42:00.430
I'm sure the Mallachis will try
and get them in a crunch.

42:02.470 --> 42:03.470
Are you ready, sweetheart?

42:03.470 --> 42:05.560
Because we're gonna get
into this big crunch now.

42:05.560 --> 42:07.060
Now, you keep
communications open...

42:07.060 --> 42:08.280
and you protect your nose.

42:08.280 --> 42:09.810
Hey, sweetheart,

42:09.810 --> 42:12.150
I am serious-- I'm talking
about the nose of your car.

42:12.150 --> 42:14.230
You know, you've got
the prettiest little eyes.

42:14.230 --> 42:15.530
(loud smooch)

42:16.780 --> 42:18.820
You know, you show
the best taste, huh?

42:18.820 --> 42:19.950
Are you ready?

42:19.950 --> 42:21.290
Darling, I was born ready.

42:21.290 --> 42:24.120
Oh, man, I like your style.

42:24.120 --> 42:26.990
You shall take
the fair maiden,

42:26.990 --> 42:29.830
and I shall take
the gallant knight.

42:29.830 --> 42:31.920
Right!

42:31.920 --> 42:33.250
Which one do I have?

42:33.250 --> 42:35.170
The girl in the pink,
the pink car!

42:35.170 --> 42:36.720
I got the girl!
I got the girl!

42:36.720 --> 42:38.310
Let's go,
and just be careful, huh?

42:38.310 --> 42:39.640
I want you in one piece.

42:39.640 --> 42:41.840
Whoo! All right,
let's get 'em, huh?

42:41.840 --> 42:43.810
All right.

42:43.810 --> 42:44.900
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Arthur Fonzarelli
in car number si{\r}x</font></font></i>

42:45.400 --> 42:47.680
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">and Pinky Tuscadero
in car number seven are read{\r}y</font></font></i>

42:47.680 --> 42:50.900
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">to face the Mallachi brothers
as the derby continues{\r}.</font></font></i>

42:54.320 --> 42:56.490
(screaming, cheering)

42:56.490 --> 42:57.520
Oh... oh...

42:57.520 --> 42:58.490
MAN:
Go get 'em!

43:02.250 --> 43:04.580
I got the pink one!

43:04.580 --> 43:06.620
All right, Pinky,
watch him, watch him.

43:06.620 --> 43:08.790
Hello, Pinky!
Take this!

43:08.790 --> 43:10.670
Hey!

43:10.670 --> 43:11.510
BOTH:
Come on, Pinky!

43:13.340 --> 43:15.840
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">And Fonzie cuts off Rocc{\r}o</font></font></i>

43:15.840 --> 43:17.680
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">and keeps him
from hitting Pinky{\r}.</font></font></i>

43:17.680 --> 43:19.460
I'm on his tail,
I'm on his tail.

43:19.460 --> 43:21.020
Look out, you dirty...

43:21.020 --> 43:22.220
(laughing)

43:22.220 --> 43:24.600
Fonzarelli just missed
a close one there, folks.

43:24.600 --> 43:25.640
Hey, look at
Pinky move.
All right.

43:29.190 --> 43:30.520
Watch out for the Crunch.

43:30.520 --> 43:32.060
I saw him, I saw him.

43:32.060 --> 43:33.640
Whoa, there, easy!

43:33.640 --> 43:34.450
(laughing)

43:36.950 --> 43:39.280
All right, watch your left,
watch your left.

43:39.280 --> 43:41.900
(crowd cheering,
all talking excitedly)

43:41.900 --> 43:43.400
There she is! I got her!

43:43.400 --> 43:44.740
(tires squealing)

43:47.710 --> 43:48.790
I missed her.
All right, I'll get her.

43:48.790 --> 43:49.990
Whoa!

43:49.990 --> 43:51.580
Oh, Pretty Eyes, Pretty Eyes.

43:51.580 --> 43:53.080
I can't see those eyes
through the dust.

43:54.550 --> 43:55.470
(crashing)

43:57.250 --> 43:58.340
(crashing)
Take that!

43:58.340 --> 43:59.890
Ah, so fun!

43:59.890 --> 44:01.260
Oh, that was a good one.

44:01.260 --> 44:03.140
Well done once again!

44:03.140 --> 44:04.680
Be careful, Pinky, be careful.

44:06.760 --> 44:08.510
I'm going back at her, Myron.

44:08.510 --> 44:10.600
(tires squealing)

44:11.070 --> 44:12.980
(horn honks, Pinky groans)

44:12.980 --> 44:16.320
Oh, she took a bad hit
from Rocco.

44:16.320 --> 44:18.410
Oh, it looks like Pinky's car
is stalled.

44:18.410 --> 44:21.690
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">She's trying,
but she can't get it started{\r}.</font></font></i>

44:21.690 --> 44:22.830
What are you doing, Pinky?

44:22.830 --> 44:23.910
Fonz, I'm stuck.

44:27.200 --> 44:29.280
Ah, fair Pinky...

44:29.280 --> 44:31.290
the Mallachi Crunch.

44:33.250 --> 44:35.840
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Pinky's crawling out
to try and fix her engine{\r}.</font></font></i>

44:35.840 --> 44:37.170
No, no, no.
No!

44:37.170 --> 44:38.630
Pinky, watch it!

44:40.040 --> 44:42.050
(crashing)

44:42.050 --> 44:43.880
Pinky!

44:43.880 --> 44:45.180
(screaming)
POTSIE:
Come on!

44:47.630 --> 44:49.550
Oh, I didn't know she'd
be out on there.
(siren wailing)

44:49.550 --> 44:50.800
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">She's hurt{\r}.</font></font></i>

44:50.800 --> 44:53.890
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Pinky Tuscadero has been hurt{\r}.</font></font></i>

44:53.890 --> 44:56.610
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">This is the first casualty
in today's derby{\r}.</font></font></i>

44:56.610 --> 44:58.610
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">I just hope it's nothing
too serious{\r}.</font></font></i>

45:00.530 --> 45:02.620
Back off, will you?
Give her some air!

45:02.620 --> 45:05.120
(groaning)
Hey, look at me,
look at me.

45:05.120 --> 45:06.120
How are you?

45:06.620 --> 45:08.620
Oh, I'm all right--
it wasn't high.
Yeah, yeah.

45:08.620 --> 45:11.130
You better let the doc
check you out, all right?

45:11.130 --> 45:12.630
Oh, I wanted us to win.

45:12.630 --> 45:14.630
Hey, don't worry about
it, us will win.

45:14.630 --> 45:16.630
(groans, gasps)

45:18.130 --> 45:19.130
Kill 'em, winner.

45:19.130 --> 45:20.630
Yeah, thanks.

45:20.630 --> 45:22.640
All right, listen, you
look after Pinky, huh?

45:22.640 --> 45:24.640
I'll take care of
the Mallachis, huh?

45:26.140 --> 45:27.640
All right, you be
careful with her.

45:27.640 --> 45:28.590
All right,
here, take her.

45:28.590 --> 45:29.760
FONZIE:
Easy...

45:29.760 --> 45:31.150
Easy.

45:32.810 --> 45:35.150
RICHIE:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Pinky appears to be okay{\r},</font></font></i>

45:35.150 --> 45:36.820
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">but as
a precautionary measure{\r},</font></font></i>

45:36.820 --> 45:38.690
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">they're rushing her
to the hospital for X-rays{\r}.</font></font></i>

45:43.820 --> 45:45.740
(engine starts)

45:55.920 --> 45:57.920
Did you see that look
on Fonzie's face?

45:57.920 --> 45:59.010
RICHIE:
Fonzie is
really angry!

45:59.510 --> 46:01.010
Fonzie, are you
all right?

46:01.510 --> 46:04.510
(siren wailing)

46:06.960 --> 46:09.270
I've never seen
such determination.

46:09.270 --> 46:10.850
Well, I just hope
determination is enough,

46:10.850 --> 46:12.600
because it's still
two against one.

46:36.910 --> 46:38.380
(engine starting)

46:38.380 --> 46:40.460
This is for you, Pinky.

46:49.470 --> 46:51.980
♪ Good-bye gray sky,
hello, blue ♪

46:51.980 --> 46:54.900
♪ There's nothing can hold me
when I hold you ♪

46:54.900 --> 46:57.400
♪ It feels so right,
it can't be wrong ♪

46:57.400 --> 46:59.820
♪ Rockin' and rollin'
all week long ♪

46:59.820 --> 47:02.240
♪ These days are ours ♪

47:05.240 --> 47:07.740
♪ These days are ours ♪

47:10.580 --> 47:21.640
♪ These happy days
are yours and mine ♪

